<p style="text-align: justify;">At the age of 19 after graduating from the high school football club(Takigawa Daini High school) Okazaki Â signed up for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shimizu_S-Pulse" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shimizu S-pluse</a> a Japanese football clubÂ  and through which he made his first appearance in Â Japanese league. He was able to score three goalsÂ  with 13 appearance Â for his first season. He established himself as a good and important player for this club and continued his journey scoring several goals and was transferred Â to Germanâ€™s club <a href="https://www.vfb.de/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vfb Stuttgart</a> that started his career at <a href="https://www.bundesliga.com/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bundesliga</a> in 2011.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">His first contract with<a href="https://www.vfb.de/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Vfb</a> Stuttgart was for three and a half years. His debut game for <a href="https://www.vfb.de/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">vfb</a> was in Europa league against <a href="https://www.slbenfica.pt/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Benfica</a> and he was not able to score for his club on his debut match. He also made his<a href="https://www.bundesliga.com/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Â Bundesligaâ€™s</a> debut appearance against <a href="https://www.bayer04.de/en-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bayer 04 Leverkusen</a> and again he was not able to score for his clubÂ  however he scored his first goal for <a href="https://www.vfb.de/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vfb</a> against <a href="https://www.hannover96.de/en/homepage.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Hannover 96</a>. His goal against<a href="https://www.hannover96.de/en/homepage.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Hannover 96</a> on 19<sup>th</sup> February 2012 was selected as the goal of the month in <a href="https://www.bundesliga.com/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">BundesligaÂ </a>then, he moved to<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1._FSV_Mainz_05" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> 1. FSV Mainz 05</a>Â on 2013 and made his debut goal against his former club<a href="https://www.vfb.de/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Â Vfb</a>. Consequently he established himself as one of the best japanase players in the history ofÂ <a href="https://www.bundesliga.com/en" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Bundesliga</a>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Okazaki again moved to<a href="https://www.premierleague.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> premier league</a> side to <a href="https://www.lcfc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Leicester City</a> in 2015 and made his debut goal against <a href="https://www.whufc.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">West Ham United</a>. He became the second Japanese player after <a href="http://wikiceleb.com/shinji-kagawa/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Shinji Kagawa</a> to win the <a href="https://www.premierleague.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">premier league</a> title. His career shows that he moved to <a href="https://www.lcfc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Leicester city</a> to win the <a href="https://www.premierleague.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">premier league</a> title. He has scored all together of 108 goals for his clubs and 17 goals for the club <a href="https://www.lcfc.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Leicester</a>.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Okazaki has scored 50 goals in his international career and 15 goals in the year 2009 for his country Japan. He has scored against Argentina and won the game with the final score 1-0 in international friendly. He has also scored three international hat-tricks. As japan has qualified for Fifa world cup 2018 Russia OkazakiÂ  will be playing for Japan in World cup 2018 too.</p>
